    {
      "id": "fc660a4e12926850d7c03149eccbc640",
      "url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=49022990",
      "title": "Ask HN: Is there a website that tracks excessive writes to SSDs in OS/app betas?",
      "content": "<p>If not, why not?<p>That way, people can choose whether they want to install various software betas based on how much SSD wear they are willing to accept.<p>And since this data would be made public and available in one place, software developers would be more careful about excessive logging in their betas.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Comments URL: <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=49022990\">https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=49022990</a></p>\n<p>Points: 10</p>\n<p># Comments: 11</p>",
